 ‚úÖ Doctyoe with Each Field =====



1. Bill of Materials (BOM) ----  

1Ô∏è‚É£ PRODUCTION ITEM SECTION

| Field                                      | Meaning                                                |
| ------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------ |
| Item                                       | Finished product to be manufactured/repacked.          |
| Item UOM                                   | Unit of measure of finished product.                   |
| Quantity                                   | Quantity of finished product produced per BOM.         |
| Is Active                                  | BOM is usable in manufacturing.                        |
| Is Default                                 | System will use this BOM automatically.                |
| Allow Alternative Item                     | Allows raw material substitution.                      |
| Set rate of sub-assembly item based on BOM | Use BOM cost for sub-assemblies instead of item price. |
| Project                                    | Link BOM to a project.                                 |


here,

1. Set rate of sub-assembly item based on BOM :
- In ERPNext, when an item inside a BOM has its own BOM (a sub-assembly), the system automatically sets its rate using the total cost calculated 
  from that sub-assembly‚Äôs BOM instead of using the item‚Äôs purchase rate or valuation rate.

‚≠ê Expanded Definition (Clear & Practical)
When building a BOM in ERPNext:
- If an item is a raw material ‚Üí ERPNext uses its valuation rate or last purchase rate.
- If an item is a sub-assembly (it has its own BOM) ‚Üí ERPNext uses the total cost of its BOM as the rate.


ERPNext calculates this by:
- Reading the sub-assembly‚Äôs BOM.
- Summing all material + operation costs.
- Assigning this cost as the ‚ÄúRate‚Äù in the parent BOM.

For example, 

finished good BOM - 

| Sub-Assembly / Raw Item | Qty | Rate Source    | Rate | Amount |
| ----------------------- | --- | -------------- | ---- | ------ |
| Motherboard Assembly    | 1   | Valuation Rate | 91   | 91     |
| Screen Assembly         | 1   | **From BOM**   | 60   | 60     |
| Keyboard                | 1   | Valuation Rate | 15   | 15     |
| Battery Pack            | 1   | Valuation Rate | 30   | 30     |
| SSD                     | 1   | Valuation Rate | 20   | 20     |
| Laptop Body             | 1   | Valuation Rate | 25   | 25     |
| Charger                 | 1   | Valuation Rate | 12   | 12     |
| Packaging Box           | 1   | Valuation Rate | 5    | 5      |

now for screen assembly we have BOM for that

| Item      | Qty | Rate | Amount |
| --------- | --- | ---- | ------ |
| LCD Panel | 1   | 50   | 50     |
| Touch Pad | 1   | 10   | 10     |

üëâ Total Screen Cost = 60

 ERPNext sets:  Rate(Screen Assembly) = 60


---------------------

2. ALternative items

In ERPNext, ‚ÄúAlternative Item in BOM‚Äù is always for raw materials or components, NOT for finished goods or sub-assemblies.

When creating a Work Order, ERPNext checks stock:
- If Battery Pack A is in stock ‚Üí use it
- If Battery Pack A is out of stock ‚Üí ERPNext shows:

‚ÄúAlternative Item Available: Battery Pack B‚Äù
You can choose Battery Pack B with one click.

note :
- Battery A and Battery B must both be RAW MATERIAL items.
- you need to set it in the Item Alternative doctype, Then in the BOM, Battery A (raw material) can be replaced with Battery B (another raw material).


---------------------

3. Quantity
- ‚ÄúQuantity (Finished Items)‚Äù is the number of final products produced from a single execution of this BOM and its materials.‚Äù


‚≠ê Simple Rule to Remember
‚úî If BOM produces 1 item ‚Üí enter raw materials for 1 unit
‚úî If BOM produces 10 items ‚Üí enter raw materials for 10 units
‚úî ERPNext DOES NOT multiply raw materials automatically inside the BOM



üìå Important Point (Very Important)
‚ùóIn the BOM, the raw material table shows the actual quantity needed for the BOM‚Äôs total output.

ERPNext only divides or multiplies later (during costing or work order), not inside the BOM.

calculation on costing :
- ERPNext divides the raw material cost by this quantity to get the cost per finished item.

Example:

Total material cost = ‚Çπ500
Quantity = 5
Cost per unit = 500 √∑ 5 = ‚Çπ100

------------------------


2Ô∏è‚É£ COST CONFIGURATION

| Field                      | Meaning                                                                                     |
| -------------------------- | -------------------------------------------                                                 |
| Rate of Materials Based On | How raw material prices are selected. ( valuation rate, last purchase rate, price list)     |
| Currency                   | Currency in which BOM costs are calculated.                                                 |


3Ô∏è‚É£ RAW MATERIALS (Items Table)


| Field     | Meaning                            |
| --------- | ---------------------------------- |
| Item Code | Raw material used in production.   |
| Qty       | Quantity of raw material required. |
| UOM       | Unit of measure of raw material.   |
| Rate      | Cost of one unit of raw material.  |
| Amount    | Total cost of raw material row.    |


4Ô∏è‚É£ OPERATIONS TAB


| Field                     | Meaning                                   |
| ------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| With Operations           | Enable operation and workstation costing. |
| Transfer Material Against | Determines how materials are issued. ( work order, job card )     |
| Routing                   | Predefined group of operations.           |

Operations Child Table

| Field            | Meaning                                         |
| ---------------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
| Operation        | Step performed during manufacturing.            |
| Workstation Type | Machine/workstation used.                       |
| Operation Time   | Time required to perform operation.             |
| Fixed Time       | Minimum time required irrespective of quantity. |
| Operating Cost   | Cost of performing operation.                   |


OR


| Field                                   | Meaning                                                                                                                         |
| --------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Finished Goods based Operating Cost** | Operation cost is calculated **per finished item**, not per operation/time.                                                     |
| **Operating Cost Per BOM Quantity**     | Enter total operating cost for the BOM output. If filled, ERPNext **ignores operation-wise cost** and uses this value directly. |

here,

1. Finished Goods based Operating Cost
- If this is checked, ERPNext calculates the operating (labor/overhead) cost per finished item, instead of calculating it based on " operation time or workstation rate ".

ex. 
BOM produces 10 laptops

  Total operating cost = ‚Çπ500

If this setting is ON:
- Operating cost per laptop = 500 √∑ 10 = ‚Çπ50

--------------------

2. Operating Cost Per BOM Quantity
- This is the total operating (labor/overhead) cost for producing the entire BOM quantity. If you enter a value here, ERPNext will ignore 
  operation-wise time and workstation costs and use this value directly.
  
‚≠ê Simplest Explanation
You manually tell ERPNext: üëâ ‚ÄúThis whole BOM costs X amount in labor/operations.‚Äù
- ERPNext will not calculate operation cost automatically.  

so it is : A manual override field to directly set the total operating cost for the BOM‚Äôs output.

note :
1. 
- Operating Cost Per BOM Quantity is for the whole BOM batch, not per finished item.
 
So if your BOM produces 2 laptops, and you set: Operating Cost Per BOM Quantity = 200


Then ERPNext will treat it like this:
- Total operating cost for producing 2 laptops = 200
- Operating cost per laptop = 200 √∑ 2 = 100


---------------------


3. Transfer Material Against
‚úÖ When Transfer Material Against = Work Order
- You usually create ONE stock entry (Material Transfer for Manufacture).
- This stock entry transfers all required raw materials for the entire production batch.
- Materials are issued once per Work Order.

‚úî One Work Order ‚Üí One Material Transfer for Manufacture

üëâ Example
1 Work Order ‚Üí 1 Material Transfer for Manufacture ‚Üí All Job Cards can begin.


‚úÖ When Transfer Material Against = Job Card
- You create a stock entry for each operation, based on the Job Card.

- Each job card can require different materials.
- Materials are issued operation-wise, not all at once.

‚úî Multiple operations ‚Üí Multiple Material Transfer for Manufacture entries

Example:
If you have 3 operations in the routing:
Cutting
Welding
Painting

You may end up creating 3 stock entries, one per job card.

üëâ Example
Operation 1 ‚Üí 1 Material Transfer for Manufacture
Operation 2 ‚Üí 1 Material Transfer for Manufacture
Operation 3 ‚Üí 1 Material Transfer for Manufacture

- always Stock Entry Type = Material Transfer for Manufacture



5Ô∏è‚É£ SCRAP & PROCESS LOSS

WHAT IS SCRAP ITEM ? 

When you manufacture something:
- Some material is used
- Some material becomes scrap (waste, off-cuts, unusable pieces, leftover material)
- ERPNext allows you to define this scrap in the BOM so it can be:

‚úî Tracked
‚úî Added to stock (if reusable)
‚úî Valued
‚úî Sold later


Scrap Items Table

| Field     | Meaning                          |
| --------- | -------------------------------- |
| Item Code | Scrap generated from production. |
| Qty       | Quantity of scrap.               |
| Rate      | Value of scrap.                  |

Process Loss

| Field          | Meaning                                        |
| -------------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
| % Process Loss | Percentage of material lost during production. |


6Ô∏è‚É£ MORE INFO TAB

| Field                       | Meaning                                |
| --------------------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| Item Name                   | Name of finished product (read-only).  |
| Item Description            | Description of finished product.       |
| Quality Inspection Required | Enable quality check after production. |
| Quality Inspection Template | Template used for inspection.          |


7Ô∏è‚É£ WEBSITE TAB

| Field               | Meaning                                        |
| ------------------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
| Show in Website     | Display this BOM/item on website.              |
| Route               | Website URL for this item.                     |
| Website Image       | Image shown on website.                        |
| Website Description | HTML description of the item.                  |
| Show Items          | Show raw materials on website page.            |
| Show Operations     | Show manufacturing operations on website page. |



