3Ô∏è‚É£ SUB ASSEMBLY ITEMS

Checkboxes

| Field                                 | Meaning                                                |
| ------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------ |
| **Consolidate Sub Assembly Items**    | Combine same sub-assembly items from multiple BOMs.    |
| **Skip Available Sub Assembly Items** | Do not create MRP for sub-assemblies already in stock. |

Other Fields

| Field                      | Meaning                                             |
| -------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------- |
| **Sub Assembly Warehouse** | Warehouse where sub-assembly stock will be checked. |
| **Get Sub Assembly Items** | Button to fetch required sub-assembly items.        |

Sub Assembly Items Table

| Field                      | Meaning                                               |
| -------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| **Sub Assembly Item Code** | Sub-assembly required for production.                 |
| **Target Warehouse**       | Warehouse where sub-assembly will be produced/stored. |
| **Schedule Date**          | Planned date of sub-assembly production.              |
| **Required Qty**           | Quantity required.                                    |
| **BOM No**                 | BOM for the sub-assembly.                             |
| **Manufacturing Type**     | Indicates whether in-house or subcontracted.          |

here in the table,

- You don‚Äôt need to manually enter data in these tables.
- ERPNext automatically fetches all required items using the ‚ÄúGet Items‚Äù buttons.

so When you click Get Sub Assembly Items, system auto-fetches all sub-assemblies from the BOM tree.
‚û°Ô∏è No manual entry required.

here,

1. Consolidate Sub Assembly Items
- merges the same sub-assembly items into a single combined requirement so you can create one Work Order for the total quantity.

   If multiple finished products need the same sub-assembly, ERPNext will merge them into one line instead of many separate lines.


üß© Think of it like this

You are making:
 Laptop A = 5 units
 Laptop B = 3 units

Both laptops use the same sub-assembly: Battery Pack

- Without consolidation, ERPNext lists this:

Battery Pack ‚Äì 5 (for Laptop A)
Battery Pack ‚Äì 3 (for Laptop B)

- With consolidation ON:

Battery Pack ‚Äì 8 (combined)


If an item has a BOM ‚Üí ERPNext thinks it must be MANUFACTURED ‚Üí so it creates a Work Order.
If an item has NO BOM ‚Üí ERPNext thinks it is a RAW MATERIAL ‚Üí no Work Order.

That's it.


üß© Case 1 ‚Äî Battery has no BOM

Battery = raw material
Expected behavior:

‚ùå No Work Order
‚úî Only Material Request (purchase/transfer)

üß© Case 2 ‚Äî Battery has its own BOM

Battery Pack = assembled from cells and wiring
Battery Pack = sub-assembly
Expected behavior:

‚úî ERPNext will create a Work Order
‚ùå It will NOT show it in raw materials
‚úî It will show it under Sub-Assembly Items



note : 
‚úÖ If Battery is a Sub-Assembly (has its own BOM)

AND you use it as a raw material inside Laptop BOM‚Ä¶**
üëâ ERPNext WILL create a Work Order for each required Battery.

Why?

Because ERPNext thinks: ‚ÄúBattery is not a raw material. Battery has a BOM, so it must be MANUFACTURED.‚Äù

So yes:

‚úî If you link a sub-assembly item inside Laptop BOM
‚úî ERPNext will generate Work Orders for that sub-assembly
‚úî Either 1 work order per unit or a consolidated one (if consolidation is ON)




üß© Example
Battery Pack (Sub-Assembly)
- Has BOM
- Requires lithium cells, wiring, BMS module
- Marked as ‚ÄúIs Manufactured Item‚Äù

Laptop BOM:
- Uses Battery Pack as a component

Production Plan:
- If you produce 5 laptops ‚Üí

ERPNext will say: Make 5 Battery Packs (Work Order)


Because Battery Pack is not a raw material,
it is a manufactured sub-assembly.


so in simple ::::::::::

‚úÖ 1Ô∏è‚É£ When you TICK ‚ÄúConsolidate Sub Assembly Items‚Äù

ERPNext will create ONE Work Order for the total required quantity.

Example:

You produce 5 Laptops
Each laptop needs 1 Battery Pack (sub-assembly)

With Consolidate ON:

üëâ ERPNext creates ONE Work Order:

Work Order:
Battery Pack ‚Äì Qty: 5

‚úî Clean
‚úî Single WO
‚úî Easy to manage

You are right.



‚ùå 2Ô∏è‚É£ When you DO NOT TICK ‚ÄúConsolidate Sub Assembly Items‚Äù
ERPNext creates SEPARATE Work Orders for each demand.

Example:
Laptop 1 ‚Üí Battery Pack (WO 1)
Laptop 2 ‚Üí Battery Pack (WO 2)
Laptop 3 ‚Üí Battery Pack (WO 3)
Laptop 4 ‚Üí Battery Pack (WO 4)
Laptop 5 ‚Üí Battery Pack (WO 5)

üëâ 5 different Work Orders
(very messy)

You are right again.	

Final THought : ‚úÖ ‚ÄúConsolidate Sub Assembly Items‚Äù is ONLY useful when your main BOM contains sub-assemblies.



 
--------------------------

2. Skip Available Sub Assembly Items

:) If this checkbox is ON (‚úî Skip Available Sub Assembly Items):

ERPNext says: ‚ÄúWe already have 4 in stock‚Ä¶

- So create Work Order only for the missing 6.‚Äù
- It creates: Work Order ‚Üí Battery Pack ‚Üí Qty 6

:) If this checkbox is OFF (‚ùå unchecked):

- ERPNext ignores the stock and creates:

Work Order ‚Üí Battery Pack ‚Üí Qty 10

- Even though 4 are already available ‚Äî this wastes resources.


------------------------------

Sub Assembly Warehouse = The warehouse where ERPNext checks stock of sub-assembly items



4Ô∏è‚É£ MATERIAL REQUEST PLANNING

Main Checkboxes

| Field                                                | Meaning                                                     |
| ---------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Include Non Stock Items**                          | Also include items not maintained in stock.                 |
| **Include Subcontracted Items**                      | Include items supplied to subcontractors.                   |
| **Consider Minimum Order Qty**                       | Apply supplier‚Äôs minimum order quantity rule.               |
| **Include Safety Stock in Required Qty Calculation** | Add safety stock to required raw materials.                 |
| **Ignore Available Stock**                           | Create material request even if stock is already available. |

Other Fields

| Field                              | Meaning                                                     |
| ---------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Raw Materials Warehouse**        | Warehouse used for raw material availability check.         |
| **Get Raw Materials for Purchase** | Button to fetch required purchase items.                    |
| **Get Raw Materials for Transfer** | Button to fetch items to be transferred between warehouses. |


Raw Materials Table ( in this we have two button : Get Raw Material For Purchase / Transfer but select warehouse to check )

| Field                   | Meaning                             |
| ----------------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| **Item Code**           | Raw material required.              |
| **For Warehouse**       | Target warehouse for raw material.  |
| **Type**                | Whether to Purchase or Transfer.    |
| **Plan to Request Qty** | Quantity system will request.       |
| **Qty As Per BOM**      | Quantity required according to BOM. |
| **Required By**         | Date raw material is needed.        |

here diffrence b/w plan to request qty & qty as per bom

| Field                   | Meaning                                                                                       |
| ----------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Qty As Per BOM**      | Exact requirement from BOM only. No adjustments.                                              |
| **Plan to Request Qty** | Final quantity after applying safety stock, stock availability, MOQ, transfer/purchase logic. |

- ERPNext automatically decides whether you need to Purchase or Transfer.

here,

1. Include Non Stock Items

Meaning:
If some items are services or non-stock (not stored in warehouse), include them in planning.

Example: Design Fee, Inspection Service, Packaging Service
- Normally they are not stock items, but checking this will include them.


- ERPNext normally plans only stock items (items stored in a warehouse).
But sometimes your BOM contains items that are: Services (not physical), Non-stock items (not stored in warehouse), One-time charges

If you check Include Non Stock Items, ERPNext will ALSO plan these items during Material Request Planning.


‚≠ê Why is this useful?
Because some production processes cannot continue without these services.

Example:
- Laptop motherboard must be programmed, done by an external service.
- Laptop body requires painting, done by a painting vendor.
- Packaging boxes need printing, done by a print shop.

If ERPNext ignores these services, your production plan will be incomplete.

----------------

2. Include Subcontracted Items

Meaning:
Include items that must be sent to a subcontractor.

Example:
- If Motherboard Assembly is completed by a subcontractor ‚Üí ERPNext will consider raw materials for subcontracting.

‚≠ê What happens when checkbox is ON?

ERPNext will:

‚úî Calculate how many IC chips are needed
‚úî Plan to buy them
‚úî Plan to send them to subcontractor
‚úî Ensure subcontractor can produce the sub-assembly
‚úî Ensure you receive the finished motherboard
‚úî Ensure final laptop assembly continues smoothly

This makes the entire production flow correct.

üß© REAL Example (very simple)

You want to produce 10 laptops.

Motherboard Assembly (subcontracted) needs:
1 PCB Board
5 IC chips
20 capacitors

If the checkbox is ON:

ERPNext calculates total qty needed:
PCB Board = 10
IC Chips = 50
Capacitors = 200

- ERPNext creates Material Requests to buy these items.
- You send them to subcontractor ‚Üí subcontractor builds motherboard ‚Üí you assemble laptop.

----------------

3. Consider Minimum Order Qty

Meaning:
Apply supplier‚Äôs MOQ rule.

Example:
You need 5 screens
Supplier‚Äôs MOQ = 10
ERPNext will request 10, not 5.

where set this MOQ :

1. Go to: Item
2. Open the item (example: Screen)
3. Scroll to section: Purchase
4. Inside it you will see: Item Supplier Table
5. In each supplier row you will find a field called: Minimum Order Qty


----------------

4. Include Safety Stock in Required Qty Calculation

Meaning:
Add safety stock to the required raw materials.

Example:
BOM requires 20 batteries
Safety stock = 5
ERPNext will request 25 batteries.


In Item Master, the item has: Safety Stock = 5 Batteries
----------------

5. Ignore Available Stock

Meaning:
Create Material Request even if you already have stock.

Example:
You need 10 SSDs
Stock available = 20

If this is ON:
ERPNext will still create a request for 10 more.
Useful when you want fresh materials or dedicated stock.

----------------

5Ô∏è‚É£ OTHER DETAILS
| Field                  | Meaning                                             |
| ---------------------- | --------------------------------------------------- |
| **Total Planned Qty**  | Sum of all planned quantities in the plan.          |
| **Total Produced Qty** | Total quantity actually produced (auto-calculated). |
| **Status**             | Current status (Draft, Submitted, Completed, etc.). |


----------------------------------

other fields :  

1. 
Consolidate Sales Order Items
- When this checkbox is enabled, ERPNext will:
‚úî Merge / combine identical items from different Sales Orders
‚úî Create ONE Work Order for total quantity instead of multiple
‚úî Reduce duplication
‚úî Plan production more efficiently


Suppose you have 3 Sales Orders

| Sales Order | Item   | Qty |
| ----------- | ------ | --- |
| SO-001      | Laptop | 10  |
| SO-002      | Laptop | 5   |
| SO-003      | Laptop | 7   |

üëâ With Consolidate Sales Order Items = Checked
ERPNext will combine all 3: Laptop ‚Üí total qty 22

And create one Work Order for 22 units
(or as many as allowed by maximum work order quantity).


üëâ With Consolidate Sales Order Items = Unchecked
- ERPNext will create separate Work Orders:
Work Order for 10
Work Order for 5
Work Order for 7





